# =============================================================================
# Trivy allowlist — documented accept-risk findings
# =============================================================================
# Each entry MUST include: CVE id, package, reason, tracked_in, next_review.
# Mirror the shape of scripts/audit-with-allowlist.mjs so the security
# review picks both files up together.
#
# Format: one CVE id per line; trailing `#` comment captures the rationale.
# Trivy reads only the first whitespace-delimited token, so the comment
# is human-only and does not affect filtering.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Allowlisted CVEs — these mirror entries in scripts/audit-with-allowlist.mjs.
# When that file is updated, this one must be too (and vice-versa).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# wave-L upgrade (W1, 2026-05-17): CVE-2026-44902
# (@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node + @opentelemetry/sdk-node,
# GHSA-q7rr-3cgh-j5r3) is patched by sdk-node 0.218.0 +
# auto-instrumentations-node 0.76.0 in this PR — the allowlist entry
# has been removed alongside the matching entries in
# scripts/audit-with-allowlist.mjs.

CVE-2026-39356 # package=drizzle-orm, severity=HIGH
#   reason:       SQL injection via improperly escaped identifier strings —
#                 only reachable when callers pass tenant-controlled
#                 identifier strings into raw SQL. Codebase audit confirmed
#                 all our calls use Drizzle's typed builders.
#   tracked_in:   Docs/DEP_HYGIENE.md (drizzle-orm 0.45 migration)
#   next_review:  2026-Q2

CVE-2026-4800 # package=lodash, severity=HIGH
#   reason:       Arbitrary code execution via `_.template` accepting
#                 untrusted input. Codebase audit confirmed no `_.template`
#                 calls accept tenant-controlled input. The patched
#                 version >=4.18.0 does not exist on npm (latest is 4.17.21).
#   tracked_in:   Docs/DEP_HYGIENE.md (lodash migration)
#   next_review:  2026-Q3

CVE-2025-59840 # package=vega + vega-expression, severity=HIGH
#   GHSA-7f2v-3qq3-vvjf
#   reason:       Vega XSS via expressions abusing toString calls in
#                 environments using the VEGA_DEBUG global variable.
#                 BORJIE never sets VEGA_DEBUG in production; C3
#                 generative-UI pipeline server-emits Vega-Lite specs
#                 that ajv-check against the v5 JSON schema BEFORE
#                 render. LLM never reaches the expression-builder
#                 surface. vega 6.x is a major version with a different
#                 rendering pipeline; sticking with 5.x until upstream
#                 lands a 5.x backport or we plan the 6.x migration.
#   tracked_in:   Docs/DEP_HYGIENE.md (vega 6.x migration)
#   next_review:  2026-Q4
#   wave-L audit: 2026-05-17 (W4) re-verified all three mitigations —
#                 VEGA_DEBUG grep returns ZERO hits outside the
#                 allowlist files; ajv validates every Vega-Lite spec
#                 before render in both the server render-block and
#                 the client VegaChart consumer; no setdata call sites
#                 exist in genui/ or render-blocks/. Mitigations hold.

CVE-2025-66648 # package=vega-functions, severity=HIGH
#   GHSA-m9rg-mr6g-75gm
#   reason:       vega-functions XSS via setdata function. setdata-XSS
#                 requires attacker-controlled data injection into a
#                 setdata call site, which doesn't exist in our pipeline.
#                 C3 server emits + ajv-validates Vega-Lite specs; LLM
#                 never reaches client-side setdata; setdata is invoked
#                 only by the Vega runtime against server-controlled
#                 data payloads.
#   tracked_in:   Docs/DEP_HYGIENE.md (vega 6.x migration)
#   next_review:  2026-Q4
#   wave-L audit: 2026-05-17 (W4) confirmed — VegaChart uses the
#                 declarative `data: { values: props.data }` injection
#                 pattern and never invokes setdata client-side.

CVE-2026-25223 # package=fastify, severity=HIGH
#   GHSA-jx2c-rxcm-jvmq
#   reason:       Fastify Content-Type header tab-character validation
#                 bypass. Six internal services pin fastify ^4.27.0
#                 (sleep-pass-orchestrator, parcel-service,
#                 onboarding-orchestrator, outcomes-metering,
#                 field-capture-service, voice-agent). All six are
#                 internal-only — they sit behind the api-gateway BFF and
#                 only accept service-to-service traffic with the agent-
#                 platform mTLS-style JWT, never raw public Content-Type
#                 headers. The fix lands in fastify 5.7.2; fastify 4 → 5
#                 is a major-version migration (Node 20 baseline + error-
#                 handler signature changes) deferred to its own PR.
#   tracked_in:   Docs/DEP_HYGIENE.md (fastify 5.x migration)
#   next_review:  2026-Q3
